    "He knew that God's mercy was enough, and he knew that he was blessed to be a part of it.",
    "As the sun set over the city of Nineveh, Jonah closed his eyes and prayed.",
    "He prayed for the people of Nineveh.",
    "were mysterious and inscrutable, but they were always guided by mercy and grace.",
    "And as Jonah looked up at the sky, he realized that just as the winds and weather had been guided by God's hand, so too was his own life."
